  "The model can only simulate volcanic events": "",
  "The model correctly represents the radiative effects of stratospheric aerosols, increasing confidence in its ability to simulate other aerosol forcing changes": "",
  "Volcanic eruptions have no lasting climate effects": "",
  "Successfully reproducing the observed cooling from Mount Pinatubo serves as a key model validation test. It demonstrates that the model correctly handles the physics of aerosol-radiation interactions, building confidence in its projections of other changes to atmospheric composition.": "",
  "An AP exam question asks students to evaluate why Earth system models project greater warming over land than over oceans. A student provides four possible explanations. Which is correct?": "",
  "Land surfaces are closer to the Sun than ocean surfaces": "",
  "Greenhouse gases only trap heat over continents": "",
  "Land has lower heat capacity than ocean water, so it warms faster, and reduced soil moisture limits evaporative cooling over land": "",
  "Oceans absorb no solar radiation": "",
  "Land warms faster than oceans because land has a much lower heat capacity (the heat is concentrated in a thin surface layer) and because limited soil moisture means less evaporative cooling. Additionally, ocean mixing distributes heat deeper, slowing surface warming.": ""
